description.narrative:
To increase capacity at all levels to provide quality and integrated HIV, SRH, TB, disability, nutrition prevention, treatment and care services to pregnant and breastfeeding women, children and adolescents, UNICEF supported 220 targeted health facilities in implementing targeted HIV testing and linkage to treatment, including in IMAM and emergency in 10 selected districts; UNICEF supported Government to integrate three key HIV interventions (Early Infant Diagnosis, pediatric testing, treatment and care) into child-centered service points. Due to challenges, UNICEF managed to support integrated SRH/HIV packages to pregnant girls in 22% out of 147 targeted health facilities in the 4 selected districts.
| Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2020
